value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the crystalline calciferous particles adhering to the otolithic membrane.
The proportion or number of the crystalline calciferous particles adhering to the otolithic membrane.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the connection of the otolithic (otoconial) membrane to the underlying neuroepithelium.
The proportion or number of turns in the spiral-shaped bony canal in the inner ear containing the hair cells that transduce sound.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the overlaying membrane of cochlear duct, an extracellular matrix of the inner ear that contacts the stereocilia bundles of specialized sensory hair cells; sound induces movement of these hair cells relative to the tectorial membrane, deflects the stereocilia, and leads to fluctuations in hair cell membrane potential, transducing sound into electrical signals.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the connection of the overlaying membrane of the cochlear duct to the cochlear epithelium or spiral limbus.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the triangular, fluid-filled space normally found between the inner and outer rows of supporting pillar cells in the organ of Corti.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the musculomembranous fold that partly separates the mouth and pharynx, located behind the hard palate.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the directed and orderly movement of white blood cells from point to point.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the nonstriated, involuntary muscle tissue lining the portion of the alimentary canal between the pharynx and stomach.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology of the part of the digestive canal through which food passes from the pharynx to the stomach during its formation and differentiation.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the lateral long bony tube of the labyrinth that is involved in the sense of balance.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the posterior segment of the long bony tube of the labyrinth that is involved in the sense of balance.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the upper, superior segment of the long bony tube of the labyrinth that is involved in the sense of balance.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the division of the spiral canal of the cochlea lying on the basal side of the spiral lamina.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the division of the spiral canal of the cochlea lying on the apical side of the spiral lamina and vestibular membrane.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the division of the spiral canal of the cochlea that contains the organ of Corti (the neuroepithelial receptor organ for hearing).
The proportion or number of the disc-like fragments of megakaryocytes that are found in the blood and function in clotting.
The two-dimensional extent of the semi-permeable membrane that encloses the cytoplasm of a pulmonary endothelial cell.

The degree of function or response of the exopeptidase that catalyses the conversion of angiotensin I to angiotensin II, a potent vasoconstrictor, and is also involved in the inactivation of bradykinin.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the process by which neurons undergo programmed cell death.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the segments of the developing neural tube.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of a slender connective tissue fiber in pulmonary tissue characterized by great elasticity.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the slender connective tissue fiber in cardiac tissue characterized by great elasticity.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the slender connective tissue fiber in tissue of the main trunk of the systemic arteries which is characterized by great elasticity.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the cavity at the caudal end of the embryonic cardiac tube in which the veins from the intra- and extraembryonic circulatory arcs unite; in the adult this becomes the portion of the right atrium known as the sinus of the vena cava.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the vessels of the highly vascular layer surrounding the yolk of an embryo; it contributes to hematopoietic circulation in mammals.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the vessels of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology during formation and differentiation of the anterior primitive cerebral vesicle; this is the most rostral of three primary vesicles of the embryonic neural tube.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of either of the broad curved wing-like expanses on each side of the sphenoid bone in adults; may exist independently in the young.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the elastic, clear, membrane-like structure, that is the outermost layer of the transparent structure of the eye responsible for focusing light rays.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the one or more of the layers of epithelial cells in the transparent structure of the eye responsible for focusing light rays.
The proportion or number of neurons in the deep lying structure of the cerebrum involved with memory storage and spatial navigation.
The proportion or number of neurons in the cerebral cortex region of the brain.

definition.value: Note that charles w. considers this distinct from degeneration

value.value: The proportion or number of neurons in the group of nuclei associated with the ability to carry out willed movements, including the caudate, putamen, nucleus accumbens, globus pallidus, substantia nigra, and subthalamic nucleus.

definition.value: Note that Charles W. considers this distinct from degeneration

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the neurons that utilize dopamine as a neurotransmitter.
The proportion or number of neurons that utilize dopamine as a neurotransmitter.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the neurons that utilize gamma-aminobutyric acid as a neurotransmitter.
The proportion or number of neurons that utilize gamma-aminobutyric acid as a neurotransmitter.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the neurons that utilize glutamate as a neurotransmitter.
The proportion or number of neurons that utilize glutamate as a neurotransmitter.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of organic, monobasic acids derived from hydrocarbons in the contractile tissue that effects movement; they are saturated and unsaturated.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the channels that secrete bile from the liver to the gall bladder and intestines.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the bile ducts.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the margins that enclose the abdominal cavity; the major part is muscular but also includes skin, subcutaneous fat, fascia and the parietal peritoneum.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the first division of the small intestine that extends from the pyloris to the junction with the jejunum.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the location or arrangement of the alimentary tract organs in relation to each other or to the body.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the location or arrangement of the large intestinal tract in relation to other organs or to the body.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the intestinal movement characterized by waves of alternate circular contraction and relaxation of the muscular walls of the bowel that move bowel contents forward.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the epithelial cell layer containing the sensory hair cells and their associated sensory nerve terminals.
